1
00:00:25,320 --> 00:00:26,640
What did you find out?

2
00:00:27,540 --> 00:00:28,528
I have the results.

3
00:00:28,920 --> 00:00:31,088
Please stay calm and listen to me carefully, K’Chat.

4
00:00:33,090 --> 00:00:34,664
Just say it, quickly.

5
00:00:35,060 --> 00:00:37,472
K’Wichai’s death wasn't an accident after all.

6
00:00:38,648 --> 00:00:39,632
What?

7
00:00:40,272 --> 00:00:42,270
The medicine was swapped by K’Jintana.

8
00:00:42,660 --> 00:00:43,984
This was a murder.

9
00:01:11,570 --> 00:01:14,456
Oh my god! K’Wichai!

10
00:01:14,488 --> 00:01:15,120
K’Wichai,

11
00:01:15,152 --> 00:01:16,680
K’Wichai, what’s wrong?

12
00:01:17,130 --> 00:01:18,200
Is anyone here?!

13
00:01:18,232 --> 00:01:19,160
What happened?

14
00:01:19,740 --> 00:01:20,840
K’Wichai

15
00:01:20,864 --> 00:01:21,784
Dad!

16
00:01:21,816 --> 00:01:22,768
K’Wichai

17
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:24,680
Dad! Dad! Dad!

18
00:01:26,740 --> 00:01:30,016
He just took his medicine and suddenly collapsed!

19
00:01:30,420 --> 00:01:30,896
K’Wichai!

20
00:01:30,936 --> 00:01:31,752
Dad!

21
00:01:31,910 --> 00:01:32,560
Dad!

22
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:33,304
Please, don't let anything happen to him.

23
00:01:33,328 --> 00:01:33,968
Dad!

24
00:01:34,016 --> 00:01:34,632
K’Wichai!

25
00:02:07,940 --> 00:02:10,504
They’ll find out after we expose what she did wrong.

26
00:02:12,330 --> 00:02:14,728
And then I’ll tell everyone that you’ve been on my side all along.

27
00:02:17,060 --> 00:02:18,400
Trust me, okay?

28
00:02:31,020 --> 00:02:35,624
In the end, you betrayed me and took your mother’s side, didn't you?

29
00:02:36,670 --> 00:02:38,024
Save your excuses.

30
00:02:38,752 --> 00:02:39,488
Get out.

31
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:58,072
Oh, you’re back.

32
00:02:59,580 --> 00:03:00,688
Where did Ran go?

33
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:02,690
I’ve looked all over the house and can’t find her anywhere.

34
00:03:03,300 --> 00:03:05,624
I was actually just coming to talk to you about that.

35
00:03:05,648 --> 00:03:09,064
It’s getting late already, and K’Ran still hasn't come to eat.

36
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:12,144
So, could you please prepare some rice soup?

37
00:03:12,168 --> 00:03:13,664
I’ll take it up to her myself.

38
00:03:13,940 --> 00:03:14,896
Okay.

39
00:03:24,140 --> 00:03:26,464
K’Wichai’s death wasn't an accident after all.

40
00:03:27,810 --> 00:03:29,720
The medicine was swapped by K’Jintana.

41
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:31,720
This was a murder.

42
00:04:18,140 --> 00:04:19,240
Time to eat.

43
00:04:24,370 --> 00:04:26,056
You aren’t mad at me anymore, P’Chat?

44
00:04:33,100 --> 00:04:34,776
Let’s eat first, then we can talk.

45
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:12,232
Are you really not mad?

46
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:24,160
If it's about the work plan, I’m not mad at you at all.

47
00:05:26,784 --> 00:05:28,780
In fact, I’m the one who should apologize.

48
00:05:30,624 --> 00:05:32,620
You’ve done so much for me, yet.

49
00:05:34,392 --> 00:05:36,390
I still failed to trust you.

50
00:05:38,936 --> 00:05:40,200
I understand.

51
00:05:42,970 --> 00:05:47,944
Honestly, I was just more afraid that you’d be mad.

52
00:06:06,312 --> 00:06:07,940
Is something wrong?

53
00:06:13,820 --> 00:06:14,440
Nothing.

54
00:06:16,260 --> 00:06:17,568
Just eat up, okay?

55
00:06:28,512 --> 00:06:32,432
Why do you love the company so much?

56
00:06:33,900 --> 00:06:36,784
Is it because of Khun Pimprapha?

57
00:06:40,880 --> 00:06:41,600
Yes.

58
00:06:44,280 --> 00:06:46,064
It was my mother’s dream.

59
00:06:49,780 --> 00:06:51,856
And I guess it’s my dream too.

60
00:06:55,370 --> 00:06:57,592
I want to continue what she started

61
00:06:59,530 --> 00:07:02,944
running the business and giving back to society.

62
00:07:09,420 --> 00:07:11,240
If I wasn't doing this,

63
00:07:12,304 --> 00:07:14,300
I can't imagine what else I’d be doing.
